[30;1m7 | [0m[35m**Attribute Anomalies:** Given anomalous observations (i.e., outliers), we can attribute them to the[0m
[30;1m8 | [0m[35mcaused them. The idea here is to ask the counterfactual question "If node x had behaved differently,[0m
[30;1m9 | [0m[35mstill have observed the anomaly?". The change in our target node quantifies how much a node contribu[0m
[30;1m10 | [0m[35mobserved anomaly. To ensure a fair attribution, this needs to be estimated systematically for differ[0m
[30;1m11 | [0m[35mof changes in nodes.[0m

[30;1m105 | [0m[35m:math:`\mathrm{Var}[Z]` is then really the contribution of corresponding noise term.[0m

[30;1m28 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m4 | [0m[35mIn GCM-based inference, fitting means, we learn the generative model of the variables in the graph f[0m
[30;1m5 | [0m[35mdata. Before we can fit the variables to data, each node in a causal graph requires a[0m
[30;1m6 | [0m[35mgenerative causal model, or a "causal mechanism". In this section, we'll dive deeper into how to use[0m
[30;1m7 | [0m[35mthis feature.[0m
[30;1m8 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m103 | [0m[35m    Specifically, the p-value is computed as the minimum of:[0m
[30;1m104 | [0m[35m    1. Twice the rank from above divided by the total number of samples.[0m
[30;1m105 | [0m[35m    2. Twice the rank from below divided by the total number of samples.[0m
[30;1m106 | [0m[35m    3. 1 (to ensure the p-value is at most 1).[0m
[30;1m107 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m16 | [0m[35mP(X = x) / 2, P(X < x) + P(X = x) / 2][0m
[30;1m17 | [0m[35m    Here, the value x is considered as part of X for the computation.[0m
[30;1m18 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m19 | [0m[35m    Comparing two NaN values are considered equal here.[0m
[30;1m20 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m21 | [0m[35m    It scores the observation based on the quantile of x with respect to the distribution of X. Here[0m
[30;1m22 | [0m[35m    sample x lies in the tail of the distribution, we want to have a large score. Since we apriori d[0m
[30;1m23 | [0m[35m    whether the sample falls on the left or right side of the median of X, we estimate the quantile [0m
